Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.36,0:05:05.78,HnF,,0,0,0,,{\pos(724,311.667)} yo?{I am?}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.28,0:05:08.53,HnF,,0,0,0,,Soy una artista marcial que sigue el camino de las artes marciales.{I am a martial artist who walks the path of martial arts.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.53,0:05:14.79,HnF,,0,0,0,,Aunque sepa actuar violenta, no puedo enseñarle eso a un novato como tú.{Even if I knew a method to practice violence, there's no way I'd teach it to an amateur like you, bro.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.28,0:05:16.42,HnF,,0,0,0,,No lo digas así.{Don't talk like that.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.74,0:05:19.68,HnF,,0,0,0,,Voy a acariciar tus senos cuando tú quieras, a partir de ahora.{I'll fondle your breasts anytime you like from now on.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.68,0:05:25.18,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿En serio? \NCon una condición así, estaría dispuesta a...{Oh, really? Well, with a condition like that, then I am also prepared to concede...}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.18,0:05:26.18,HnF,,0,0,0,,¡Nada!{Nothing!}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.18,0:05:29.28,HnF,,0,0,0,,En ningún momento voy a querer que me acaricies los senos.{There is no time when I'd like to get my breasts fondled by my brother!}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.28,0:05:31.35,HnF,,0,0,0,,Piensa en ello, Karen.{Think about it, Karen-chan.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.35,0:05:34.43,HnF,,0,0,0,,Que tu hermano te acaricie los senos cuando tú quieras,{Getting your breasts fondled by your brother when you'd like,}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.43,0:05:36.56,HnF,,0,0,0,,o que te los acaricie en cualquier momento...{vs. getting your breasts fondled when you'd not like,}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.56,0:05:37.48,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Qué sería lo mejor?{which is better?}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.51,0:05:41.11,HnF,,0,0,0,,¡Oh! Preferiría cuando yo quisiese.{Oh! I'd prefer getting fondled when I'd like!}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.11,0:05:43.32,HnF,,0,0,0,,Es obvio ahora que lo has dicho.{It's obvious once you compare them!\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.32,0:05:45.71,HnF,,0,0,0,,¡Ahí estamos! Eres muy listo.{That's my bro, you're so smart!}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.07,0:05:47.82,HnF,,0,0,0,,{That's my Karen-chan.}¡Esa es mi hermana!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.82,0:05:48.57,HnF,,0,0,0,,Tan tonta como siempre.{You're so dumb}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.36,0:05:50.33,HnF,,0,0,0,,Ya lo tengo.{Alright, got it.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.33,0:05:55.08,HnF,,0,0,0,,No suelo tener aprendices, \Npero haré una excepción contigo.{It's not my policy to take on apprentices, but I'll make a special exception for my bro.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.54,0:05:57.29,HnF,,0,0,0,,Entonces por ejemplo, ¿qué harías{So what would you do for example?}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.29,0:06:02.09,HnF,,0,0,0,,si tuvieras que golpear a una persona que es mucho más fuerte que tú?{If you'd want to land a punch on a person who is clearly stronger than you, what would you do?}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.09,0:06:03.09,HnF,,0,0,0,,¡Sería imposible!{It's impossible!}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.09,0:06:05.76,HnF,,0,0,0,,Ahora en serio.{No, seriously.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.76,0:06:11.35,HnF,,0,0,0,,Según ese ejemplo, sería complicado enfrentarte a esa persona, ¿no?{Under those terms, it'd be difficult to get in a punch versus that person, wouldn't it?}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.35,0:06:13.47,HnF,,0,0,0,,Aunque no tenga que ser un golpe limpio.{Even if it didn't have to be a clean hit.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.47,0:06:16.68,HnF,,0,0,0,,Incluso sería complicado pillarle con la guardia baja.{It'd be difficult even to get in behind their guard, wouldn't it?}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.68,0:06:19.56,HnF,,0,0,0,,Sí. Ya te dije, no tengo nada que hacer.{Yeah. I told you, I'm utterly powerless.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.74,0:06:21.56,HnF,,0,0,0,,Si existe una diferencia tan grande de habilidad,{If there's such a difference in ability,}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.56,0:06:23.07,HnF,,0,0,0,,entonces no deberías pelear.{then you just shouldn't fight them.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.07,0:06:25.82,HnF,,0,0,0,,Las artes marciales dicen que huyas.{Martial arts says you should run away.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.42,0:06:29.99,HnF,,0,0,0,,Entonces, lo que me has dicho sería algo así:{Actually, from what you've told me, I'm guessing it's like this:}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.99,0:06:37.18,HnF,,0,0,0,,Si eres capaz de darle un golpe a esa persona,\N responderá a tu pregunta, ¿es eso?{If you can land a punch on this person, they'll answer a question of yours, it's something like that, isn't it?}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.18,0:06:38.87,HnF,,0,0,0,,Sí, exacto.{Yeah, exactly.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.87,0:06:41.08,HnF,,0,0,0,,Esa es una buena deducción viniendo de ti.{That's a pretty good inference coming from you, Karen-chan.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.31,0:06:43.59,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿No es simplemente un rechazo indirectamente?{Aren't you just being refused indirectly?}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.75,0:06:47.47,HnF,,0,0,0,,Seguro que has preguntado algo comprometido.{I bet you asked something insensitive.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.47,0:06:51.22,HnF,,0,0,0,,Tal vez ha pasado de ti sin complicarse demasiado.{esto podria traducirse mejor, creo}{So maybe you've just been driven away without being exposed to the sharp edges.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.22,0:06:54.56,HnF,,0,0,0,,Y tú simplemente has estado pensando como darle un golpe a esa persona{At some point, bro, you've started to wonder only about how to get a shot in on this person}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.56,0:06:59.35,HnF,,0,0,0,,en vez de si tu pregunta va a ser respondida o no.{instead of about whether or not your question will get answered, haven't you?}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.90,0:07:05.36,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Cómo puede...?{Oh my God!}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.69,0:07:06.78,HnF,,0,0,0,,Ya veo.{I see.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.78,0:07:10.49,HnF,,0,0,0,,Así que es así como se expresa Kagenui.{So that must be how Kagenui-san expresses her adult considerations.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.07,0:07:15.05,HnF,,0,0,0,,En ese caso, ¿cómo debería responder?{Well in that case, what should I do in response?}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.05,0:07:15.87,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿¡A mí qué me cuentas!?{How should I know!}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.87,0:07:17.00,HnF,,0,0,0,,¡Piénsalo tú solo!{Think about it yourself!}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.80,0:07:20.40,HnF,,0,0,0,,Pero si fuera tú...{But if it were me,}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.40,0:07:25.26,HnF,,0,0,0,,Haría lo posible para que esa persona no se diera cuenta.{I'd do my best so that this person, who was so considerate of me, wouldn't lose face.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.60,0:07:33.22,HnF,,0,0,0,,Al menos, que no se diera cuenta de que descubrí su excusa sobre la pelea.{At the least, I'd make sure that they didn't find out that I saw through their excuse to propose the fight.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.96,0:07:39.48,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Para que Kagenui no vea que estoy intentando responder indirectamente.{In order to give nonchalant concern to Kagenui-san by way of hiding my intention to respond to her sentiment,}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.48,0:07:43.96,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Necesitaré algún tipo de excusa cuando la vea.{I'll need some kind of excuse for when I face her.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.66,0:07:52.61,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Eso significa que tengo que pensar en alguna forma de darle un golpe,{So that means I'll have to think of some way to get a shot in on her,}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.61,0:07:55.10,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,pero no de ganar, sino de perder elegantemente.{not to win against her, but to lose gracefully.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.86,0:07:58.97,HnF,,0,0,0,,No se me ocurre nada.{I'm at a complete standstill.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.30,0:08:03.67,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Y ahora el epílogo, o mejor dicho, la conclusión.{And now for the epilogue, or rather, the punch line.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.48,0:08:08.38,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Para crear un falso intento de ganar,{To construct a false chance of victory,}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.38,0:08:14.47,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,estoy siguiendo lo mismo que hice cuando\N me enfrenté a ella en las vacaciones de verano.{I basically followed the same method I took when I fought against her back in summer break.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.47,0:08:16.60,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,En ese enfrentamiento{As for how I confronted that,}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.60,0:08:20.89,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,tenía a Oshino Shinobu chupándome la sangre para potenciar el vampirismo, {I had Oshino Shinobu suck my blood, boosting the vampirism in both of us,}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.89,0:08:23.39,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,haciéndome más fuerte para poder enfrentarla.{strengthening myself, and then I went to confront her.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.39,0:08:26.73,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Aunque esta vez,\N no puedo usar ese método tal cual.{This time however, I couldn't use this method as-is.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.02,0:08:29.86,HnF,,0,0,0,,Ya no puedo potenciar el vampirismo{I can no longer be allowed to raise my vampirism}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.86,0:08:31.28,HnF,,0,0,0,,más de lo que ya tengo.{any more than it is now.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.87,0:08:34.70,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Pedí su habilidad de materializar objetos,{I borrowed her ability to materialize matter,}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.30,0:08:38.16,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,para que me hiciera una pistola.{and had her make me a pistol.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.41,0:08:42.41,HnF,,0,0,0,,{\pos(361.333,328.667)}Donuts a 100 yenes{Doughnuts 100-yen sale}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.76,0:08:43.62,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Solo traje la pistola para usarla como tal.{I brought the handgun only to use as a tool for rhetoric.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.33,0:08:46.25,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Kagenui dijo 'un golpe'.{Kagenui-san said 'one shot.'}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.08,0:08:48.13,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,'Si me das un golpe.'{'If you land one shot.'}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.15,0:08:54.34,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,En ese caso debería dar igual \Nsi es físicamente, o con una bala.{In that case it should be fine whether that one shot was from a punch or from a bullet.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.01,0:09:00.93,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Esa es la típica idea que alguien como yo pensaría.{That's just exactly the kind of simplistic idea that a fool like me would think up.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.44,0:09:06.97,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Y la parte crucial es que esta es una idea que fallará seguro.{And also, and this is the cruicial part, it was an idea that would fail 100%.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.53,0:09:13.07,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Un estudiante idiota entró al juego \Ny simplemente perdió.{An idiotic highschooler stepped up to a game and simply lost.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.07,0:09:15.15,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Así es como debería acabar.{That should be the end of that.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.79,0:09:18.66,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Una respuesta indirecta.{A sudden response to a nonchalant concern.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.66,0:09:24.58,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Antes de una respuesta sin sentido, podrá ser una respuesta elegante.{Rather, as an aftermeasure in response to a wastefulness, it should get at least a passing grade.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.81,0:09:38.55,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.70,0:09:43.30,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.69,0:09:48.56,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,La especialista invencible, \NKagenui Yozuru, ya no estaba.{The lifelong undefeated specialist, Kagenui Yodzuru, was gone.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.62,0:09:52.50,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.98,0:09:54.99,HnF,,0,0,0,,Continuará...
